channel.title: [Delta] Help!
channel.description:
Okay, so i downloaded pk jad scape and it worked fine i came back the next day and it said connection error so i just found a new client which worked fine then i went into client.java changed the ip address and now that its been compiled it says connection error please try again in.... any ideas what might be wrong i was trying to find it out and i heard something about the cache is corrupt if so is it fixable.? Any ways thanks, Heres a picture.

item.title: [Delta] Help!
item.description:
@202685 wrote:

[quote=“blazkiller123, post:2, topic:439657”]this may not be it but… i think so.

yes it’s fixable, the clients your downloading might have autocache downloaders that are built in, which means every time the client opens and loads, it checks and downloads any new versions of cache. or just attempts to. so when its gunna download the cache it’s connecting to a specific ip or website or something, and that website might not be around anymore. or something, so try and find a client that you can add your own autocache downloader, or just not have an autocache downloader at all and have your users place the cache somewhere where the client will pull it from.

hope this helps, goodluck.[/quote]

if it is infact your autocache downloader, zip your cache and upload to dropbox or something… then go into client.java and search for “class44 method67”
in that you should see a link, change it to your dropbox cache link. compile and run

Read full topic
